:"The Chair Series Review.";i:14;s:88:"The Chair series showcases the ongoing in the department of English in Pembroke College.";i:15;s:110:"The department is not the best as it used to be and Sandra Ohs Ji-Yoon Kim is given the position to lead them.";i:16;s:133:"Sandra Ohs Ji-Yoon is put in an uncomfortable position throughout the series due to various situations and she shines through it all.";i:17;s:187:"The Chair lays out an interesting exercise by examining generational divides through the prism of a college English department and the first woman of color leading it played by Sandra Oh.";i:18;s:60:"There are no simple villains in The Chair and no easy fixes.";i:19;s:126:"On the contrary the series goes out arguing that real change must go beyond the handling of a single person or a single event.";i:20;s:86:"The Chair is funny as heck with some earned moments of real emotion and a killer cast.";i:21;s:82:"Six episodes flew by and we hope to see more of Pembrokes English department soon.";i:22;s:63:"For a comedy not a single joke elicited more than a half-smile.";i:23;s:118:"For a show that takes seriously the importance of a liberal arts education its awfully dismissive of college students.";i:24;s:41:"Created by Amanda Peet Annie Julia Wyman.";i:25;s:51:"With Sandra Oh Jay Duplass Bob Balaban Nana Mensah.";i:26;s:152:"At a major university the first woman of color to become chair tries to meet the dizzying demands and high expectations of a failing English department.";i:27;s:137:"The tone of The Chair reminds me a lot of Togetherness which makes sense since Peet starred in that HBO series and Duplass co-created it.";i:28;s:96:"The Chair season 1 review a dramedy that benefits from irony A good start but more story needed.";i:29;s:61:"The Chair season 1 review a dramedy that benefits from irony.";i:30;s:82:"Its wise to accept that The Chair is closer to truth and further away from comedy.";i:31;s:285:"The writing was exceptional and the topics they brought up and talked about Just sat down and watched The Chair and finished the entire series in one sitting it was so good I had to finish it it was so well done just a perfect blend of hilarious serious and emotionally deeper moments.";i:32;s:87:"The writing was exceptional and the topics they brought up and talked about were great.";i:33;s:133:"The Sandra Oh dramedy follows the life of the first female chair of a Universitys Literature department as she navigates love single.";i:34;s:36:"See The Best Office Chairs for 2019.";i:35;s:101:"Httpbitly2DXTIe9In this video Greg gives you his initial impressions of the Steelcase Series 1 chair.";i:36;s:122:"In addition to Ohs charms Chair is a darkly funny satire skewering aspects of modern higher education with veritable glee.";i:37;s:117:"The characters are sharply written and feel real and grounded even as the events surrounding them become more crazed.";i:38;s:72:"So far reviews for Netflixs The Chair have been overwhelmingly positive.";i:39;s:72:"Its release timed as a new school year begins could not be more perfect.";i:40;s:94:"Season 1 of the series came out on August 20 and the internet has been buzzing about it since.";i:41;s:196:"My takeaway from my time with the Series 2 is that much as I love the raw functionality of good ergo chairs at this price something like the Secretlab Omega is going to be the safest bet for most.";i:42;s:28:"Substance now matches style.";i:43;s:163:"So now feels like a good time to check out Steelcases entry level ergo chair the Series 2 which at 500 is priced similarly to good quality gaming chairs to see if.";i:44;s:140:"The most important metric of our review process and the first thing that comes to mind when most people think of an office chair is comfort.";i:45;s:188:"This metric counts heaviest toward to overall score of the Series 1 and is based on the opinions of our panel of judges after trying out each of these chairs for extensive amounts of time.";i:46;s:69:"Unfortunately opinions of the Series 1 were mixed earning this chair.";i:47;s:222:"There is perhaps something admirable about the way that The Chair downplays this potentially thorny matter with Bill and the outraged student body each allowed to make their cases and as such neither side given preference.";i:48;s:157:"But refusing to take a concerted position on the scandal feels like a slight cop-out and the series lacks the wit or nuance to justify its bet-hedging after.";i:49;s:193:"The Chair is a nice tidy six-episode binge and at about three hours total it feels like a slightly extended indie-film comedy set to a soundtrack of jangly college radio hits from the likes of.";}}